<a id="PhysicsServer2DExtension"></a>

# PhysicsServer2DExtension

**Inherits:** [PhysicsServer2D](PhysicsServer2D.md) **\<** [Object](Object.md)

Provides virtual methods that can be overridden to create custom [PhysicsServer2D](PhysicsServer2D.md) implementations.

<!-- classref-introduction-group -->

## Description

This class extends [PhysicsServer2D](PhysicsServer2D.md) by providing additional virtual methods that can be overridden. When these methods are overridden, they will be called instead of the internal methods of the physics server.

Intended for use with GDExtension to create custom implementations of [PhysicsServer2D](PhysicsServer2D.md).

<a id="PhysicsServer2DExtension_private_method__space_set_debug_contacts"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

`void` **_space_set_debug_contacts**\ (\ space\: [RID](RID.md), max_contacts\: [int](int.md)\ ) <span class="virtual">virtual</span> <span class="required">required</span> [ðŸ”—](#PhysicsServer2DExtension_private_method__space_set_debug_contacts)

Used internally to allow the given `space` to store contact points, up to `max_contacts`. This is automatically set for the main [World2D](World2D.md)'s space when [SceneTree.debug_collisions_hint](SceneTree.md#SceneTree_property_debug_collisions_hint) is ``true``, or by checking "Visible Collision Shapes" in the editor. Only works in debug builds.

Overridable version of [PhysicsServer2D](PhysicsServer2D.md)'s internal ``space_set_debug_contacts`` method.

<a id="PhysicsServer2DExtension_private_method__step"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

`void` **_step**\ (\ step\: [float](float.md)\ ) <span class="virtual">virtual</span> <span class="required">required</span> [ðŸ”—](#PhysicsServer2DExtension_private_method__step)

Called every physics step to process the physics simulation. `step` is the time elapsed since the last physics step, in seconds. It is usually the same as the value returned by [Node.get_physics_process_delta_time()](Node.md#Node_method_get_physics_process_delta_time).

Overridable version of [PhysicsServer2D](PhysicsServer2D.md)'s internal ``step`` method.

<a id="PhysicsServer2DExtension_private_method__sync"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

`void` **_sync**\ (\ ) <span class="virtual">virtual</span> <span class="required">required</span> [ðŸ”—](#PhysicsServer2DExtension_private_method__sync)

Called to indicate that the physics server is synchronizing and cannot access physics states if running on a separate thread. See also [_end_sync()](PhysicsServer2DExtension.md#PhysicsServer2DExtension_private_method__end_sync).

Overridable version of [PhysicsServer2D](PhysicsServer2D.md)'s internal ``sync`` method.
